meanings.definition: To swim faster or farther than someone else.
meanings.sent1: During the race, Sarah outswam all her competitors effortlessly.
meanings.sent2: Michael outswam his friend in the pool competition.
meanings.sent3: The little fish outswam the big shark in a surprising turn of events.
meanings.sent4: The determined swimmer outswam the strong currents to reach the shore.
meanings.sent5: With powerful strokes, the athlete outswam the rest of the team to victory.

meanings.definition: To have swum faster or farther than someone else.
meanings.sent1: Yesterday, she outswam her personal best record in the pool.
meanings.sent2: The champion outswam all his opponents in the final lap.
meanings.sent3: The turtle outswam the hare in the swimming race, surprising everyone.
meanings.sent4: Her determination and practice paid off as she outswam her own doubts.
meanings.sent5: The fish outswam the net and escaped back into the open sea.
